CommonFields.Title: Poly(vinyl alcohol)/silica hybrid nanocomposites by sol-gel technique: Synthesis and properties
Author: Bandyopadhyay, A.
De Sarkar, M.
Bhowmick, A. K.
CommonFields.Location: Rubber Technology Center, Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur, India

SolventAmount.description: A 5% aqueous solution of poly(vinyl alcohol) (PVA) was prepared by dispersing 5 grams of PVA in 100 ml deionized water and then by keeping it under boiling conditions for 5 min.

Cooling.Description: After complete dissolution of the polymer, the resultant solution was cooled to room temperature (35°C).

Mixing.Description: Tetraethoxysilane (TEOS) in varying weight percentages with respect to 100 grams of the polymer, in 5 different batches, was added to the PVA solutions under stirring conditions at room temperature.

Additive.Description: After thorough mixing for 10 min, an appreciable amount of concentrated HCl was added to the resultant polymer solutions in order to adjust the pH of the medium to 1.5.

Mixing.Description: The reaction mixture was again stirred for 20 min at room temperature.

MoldingInfo.Description: After stirring, the mixture was cast over thoroughly cleaned smooth aluminum plates for gelling.

ChooseParameter.Other: Initially, the evaporation of water was controlled for one day and then the cast films were allowed to gel till they gave no weight variation. The entire gelling operation of the composite films was carried out at room temperature for 10 days.

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: Transmission electron microscopic studies were carried out using TEM (model C-12, Philips) on very thin films (100 nm) of hybrid composites, cast directly over the copper grids of 300 mesh size. The acceleration voltage was 120 kV.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: Dynamic mechanical thermal analysis (DMTA) of the hybrid composites was carried out in a DMTA IV, under tension mode. The experiments were carried out at a frequency of 1 Hz. The measurements were taken from 0 to 100°C at a heating rate of 2°C/min.

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Equipment: Nicolet Nexus Fourier Transform infrared spectrophotometer
Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: The infrared spectra of the hybrid composite films were recorded with a Nicolet Nexus Fourier Transform infrared (FTIR) spectrophotometer in ATR mode using 45^0 KRS5 prisms at room temperature.
